# Rules for Subscription UI & Paywalls

## 1. Source of truth: `GET /users/me`
Response includes `features[]`, `limits{}`, `usage{}`, `effective_tier_id`. Use `portal/js/entitlements.js` helpers — never hardcode tier names in UI.

## 2. Nav & page gating (`entitlements.js`)
Hide workspace nav items when the user lacks the required feature or has `limit === 0`:
- `product-analytics` → `product_analytics`
- `forecast` → `lstm_forecast`
- `budget-planner` / `weekly-planner` → `basic_planners` OR `unlimited_planners`
- `upload-statement` / `receipt-scanner` → `limits.statement_uploads_per_month` / `limits.receipt_scans_per_month` > 0
- Settings email connector → `email_connector`

Pages must still handle `403 UPGRADE_REQUIRED` from API as a fallback.

## 3. Global fetch interceptor
Listen for `HTTP 403` with `error_code: "UPGRADE_REQUIRED"` or `"LIMIT_EXCEEDED"` → open upgrade modal (do not hard-crash).

## 4. Paywall components
- Upgrade modal: state which feature/limit was blocked; CTA to `license.html` / billing.
- Promo entry on profile/settings → `POST /api/v1/billing/redeem-promo` → refresh profile / reload nav.

## 5. Proactive limit nudges
When `usage` approaches `limits` (e.g. 13/15 receipt scans on BASIC), show inline banner above the action button.
